Leading pan-African music service, Mdundo.com, has announced that it recorded 31 million active users across Africa in the first quarter of 2022, representing a 49 per cent growth compared with the previous quarter. Speaking to the reporters on Wednesday in Nairobi, Kenya, Head of Brand Partnerships at Mdundo, Rachel Karanu said the move solidifying the platform’s to sustained growth trajectory across the continent in the last year. She said the company attributes the growth to an ever increasing demand for easily accessible music among the young population, as well as the strategic partnerships that it continues to enter into with leading Telcos across the continent. “During the quarter the company also grew its advertising partnership footprint, working with leading brands across the continent including; Standard Chartered Bank, East Africa Breweries Limited, Nation Media Group, Airtel, Zenith Bank and 10Bet Africa. “We continue to witness an increased demand for easily accessible music, especially among the youthful mass market consumer segment across the continent, it is this demand that is the main driver of our growth. We will keep innovating around finding new ways to engage with this audience. “Our continued strategic partnerships with leading Telcos in Africa, such as MTN, Vodacom and Airtel, continue to offer us a unique platform to reach our target audience through our tailor made solutions,” she added.